    // Marketing FAQs
    'marketingHelp.faq.whatIsMarketing.q': 'What is the Marketing module?',
    'marketingHelp.faq.whatIsMarketing.a': 'The Marketing module helps you run campaigns, capture leads, and track performance. It includes campaigns, lead sources, contact results, lists, and a media gallery.',
    'marketingHelp.faq.modulesIncluded.q': 'What features are included?',
    'marketingHelp.faq.modulesIncluded.a': '• Campaigns - Multi-step lead capture forms\n• Lead Sources - Track where leads originate\n• Contact Results - Record contact outcomes\n• Lists - Segment your audience\n• Gallery - Store marketing assets\n• API - Integrate external tools',
    'marketingHelp.faq.whatIsCampaign.q': 'What is a Campaign?',
    'marketingHelp.faq.whatIsCampaign.a': 'A campaign is a marketing initiative with lead capture forms. Each campaign can have multiple steps, custom branding, and routing rules to assign leads.',
    'marketingHelp.faq.createCampaign.q': 'How do I create a campaign?',
    'marketingHelp.faq.createCampaign.a': 'Go to Campaigns and click "New Campaign". Configure the form fields, steps, branding, and routing rules. Publish to get a shareable link.',
    'marketingHelp.faq.campaignTypes.q': 'What types of campaigns can I create?',
    'marketingHelp.faq.campaignTypes.a': 'You can create:\n• Landing page forms\n• Multi-step wizards\n• Quote request forms\n• Contact forms\n• Event registrations',
    'marketingHelp.faq.leadForms.q': 'How do lead forms work?',
    'marketingHelp.faq.leadForms.a': 'Each campaign has a customizable form. Configure fields, validation, and styling. When submitted, leads are created and routed based on your rules.',
    'marketingHelp.faq.whatIsSource.q': 'What is a Lead Source?',
    'marketingHelp.faq.whatIsSource.a': 'A lead source identifies where leads come from - Facebook, Google, website, referral, etc. Track sources to measure channel effectiveness.',
    'marketingHelp.faq.configureSources.q': 'How do I configure sources?',
    'marketingHelp.faq.configureSources.a': 'Go to Sources and create entries for each channel. Add icons and colors for easy identification. Sources can be global or company-specific.',
    'marketingHelp.faq.whatIsContactResult.q': 'What is a Contact Result?',
    'marketingHelp.faq.whatIsContactResult.a': 'Contact results record what happened when you contacted a lead - answered, no answer, callback needed, etc. They can trigger automatic status changes.',
    'marketingHelp.faq.contactWorkflow.q': 'How do contact results affect workflow?',
    'marketingHelp.faq.contactWorkflow.a': 'Each result can automatically change the lead status, schedule callbacks, or trigger notifications. Configure these in Contact Results settings.',
    'marketingHelp.faq.whatIsList.q': 'What is a Marketing List?',
    'marketingHelp.faq.whatIsList.a': 'Lists are groups of contacts for targeted campaigns. Create lists by criteria or manually add contacts. Use lists for email campaigns and segmentation.',
    'marketingHelp.faq.segmentation.q': 'How do I segment my audience?',
    'marketingHelp.faq.segmentation.a': 'Create lists with specific criteria - by source, status, location, etc. Use lists to target specific segments with personalized campaigns.',
    'marketingHelp.faq.whatIsGallery.q': 'What is the Media Gallery?',
    'marketingHelp.faq.whatIsGallery.a': 'The gallery stores images, documents, and icons for use in campaigns and forms. Upload assets once and reuse across campaigns.',
    'marketingHelp.faq.uploadAssets.q': 'How do I upload assets?',
    'marketingHelp.faq.uploadAssets.a': 'Go to Gallery, click Upload, and select files. Add descriptions and tags for easy searching. Assets are available in the campaign form builder.',
    'marketingHelp.faq.apiIntegration.q': 'How do I integrate with external tools?',
    'marketingHelp.faq.apiIntegration.a': 'Use the Marketing API to send leads from external sources. Get your API key from the API section and follow the documentation.',
    'marketingHelp.faq.webhooks.q': 'Can I use webhooks?',
    'marketingHelp.faq.webhooks.a': 'Yes! Configure webhooks to send lead data to external systems when leads are created or updated. Set this up in the Integration section.',
    'marketingHelp.faq.marketingWorkflow.q': 'What is the typical marketing workflow?',
    'marketingHelp.faq.marketingWorkflow.a': '1. Create campaign with lead form\n2. Publish and share the form link\n3. Leads are captured and routed\n4. Contact leads and record results\n5. Move qualified leads to sales\n6. Analyze campaign performance',
    'marketingHelp.faq.automations.q': 'What automations are available?',
    'marketingHelp.faq.automations.a': '• Automatic lead routing by criteria\n• Status changes on contact results\n• Callback and follow-up reminders\n• List-based segmentation\n• Webhook notifications',
    'marketingHelp.faq.leadRouting.q': 'How does lead routing work?',
    'marketingHelp.faq.leadRouting.a': 'Configure routing rules in each campaign. Route by location, source, or custom criteria. Leads are automatically assigned to the right team or person.',

